  "texts": [
    "What holds for this, currently still visionary LLM holds a fortiori for less advanced available models.",
    "These models, no matter how impressive their performance, are lacking any intentions, any goals over and above the linguistic functioning for which they are being used.",
    "This means that these models are incapable of engaging in speech acts, as speech acts are always embedded in a network of intentions, of goals.",
    "One engages in a speech act to reach a certain communicative goal.",
    "In contrast, the mod-els are complex, statistically optimized, autonomously developing and functioning mathematical functions."
  ],
